MOJALEFA Tshabalala briefly appeared in court yesterday for allegedly stealing crates of beer from his work. The 35-year-old was arrested after allegedly being caught on CCTV by his employer. Bethlehem Magistrates Court, Free State postponed the case to Monday for a formal bail application. Police spokeswoman Constable Puleng Lebakeng said: “Officers received information about stationery hidden in a house in Bohlokong. On arrival at the address, stationery was found hidden in boxes. Moalosi failed to provide officers with proof of ownership.”